<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-4131] Javascript with WebSocket handles oneway methods wrong</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-4131</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When using the WebSocket transport all client-&amp;gt;server calls install a callback, and we depend on these callbacks being push()&apos;ed and shift()&apos;ed sequentially, however, oneway methods never gets a reply, and therefore the installed callback doesn&apos;t get removed, causing the callback array to get &quot;out of synchronization&quot; so to speak, and subsequent calls, now deal with the wrong callbacks, as data comes in.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To remedy this I changed the compiler/generator to send a null callback to the transport-&amp;gt;flush method for oneway methods, and then in the WebSocket transport code, make a null check and only install defined callbacks. This seem to fix it for me. I can send in patches if necessary.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;all&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
